  <div class="medium-6 columns">
      <div class="home-first--title">David Porter,<br />Associate Vice-President</div>
      <div class="home-first--subtitle">Education Support and Innovation, British Columbia Institute of Technology (BCIT)</div>

      <p>BCIT is a huge technology trades, health care, and practitioner training environment.  Many of the faculty came to open education of their own volition with three faculty authored open textbooks being published this month for the health care professions, printing trades technology, and engineering sciences.  An OER Working Committee is now spearheading the effort primarily through the library and the Learning and Teaching Center.</p>
      <p>Staff are seeing “OER” as a gift to their colleagues to be able to share resources that can be customized and made more relevant for students.  Our instructors are really driven to improve the learning experience for students while saving costs so this is a perfect synergy.</p>
