  <div class="medium-6 columns">
      <div class="home-first--title">Steve Carson,<br />Director of Operations, Open Pediatrics</div>
      <div class="home-first--subtitle">Boston Children's Hospital</div>

      <p>Simply put, open for Open Pediatrics means saving lives.   Children everywhere around the world are dying everyday because the information on how to treat them is not available.  What we strive to do is to get clinicians everywhere around the world to share the life saving treatments they have developed openly and in advance of the need by using open licenses.</p>
      <p>Formerly at MIT OpenCourseware and president of the Open Education Consortium board, it is really thrilling to be at OpenEd15 and see a community of more than 500 people gathered.  When I think back to 2003 when I first started in open education, it was a crazy idea that MIT faculty had.   Now looking forward, it is a force to be reckoned with in the education community and it is going to change the landscape and the opportunities that are available to students everywhere.</p>
  </div>
</div>
