  <div class="medium-6 columns">
      <div class="home-first--title">Jody Carson,<br />Faculty and Instructional Coach</div>
      <div class="home-first--title home-initiativies--title">Sue Tashjian, Coordinator,<br />Center for Instructional Technology and Adjunct Faculty.</div>
      <div class="home-first--subtitle">North Essex Community College, Massachusetts</div>

      <p>As the co-chairs of the college textbook taskforce, we head up the open education initiatives at NECC.  One of the biggest benefits to using OER for our courses rather than traditional textbooks is that all of our students have access to their instructional materials on day one of their classes.  They no longer have to wait for a book voucher, financial aid, or refund checks but are able to get their information on day one.  One of the most exciting things is seeing how faculty have transformed their courses by using OER.  They are really excited about the process and the courses that they have been able to customize for their students and not allow the publishers to tell them what to teach because they are the experts in the field.</p>
